cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on Natural Language Processing (NLP) and proposes a novel architecture employing Long Short-Term Memory Networks (LSTMs) to learn sub-character level representation and capture deeper level of semantic meanings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of LSTMs also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with Chinese Word Segmentation, which involves information retrieval and text analysis, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
